<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-69] currentTime returns random result if used in user program</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-69</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a problem in concurrency/Util.h &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is implementation of currentTime routine:&lt;br/&gt;
#if defined(HAVE_CLOCK_GETTIME)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
#elif defined(HAVE_GETTIMEOFDAY)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
#end&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HAVE_* defines placed in config.h, but installed version of thrift hasn&apos;t got the config.h.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example make -f Makefile.stress, gcc complains: &lt;br/&gt;
../../lib/cpp/src/concurrency/Util.h:104: warning: &apos;result&apos; is used uninitialized in this function&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the only way to resolve it is to move the function to .cpp file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
